{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"alias":"sterling-fatigable-pheasant","description":"## Why\nEpic AC1 requires a **write-time guard that rejects private-key material in an identity\nevent**. The delivered `identity` create path (ddbe / change 558) passes `keys` straight\nonto the CREATE event with no check, so a user could accidentally commit an SSH PRIVATE\nkey into the always-readable, replicated tickets store — a real (if narrow) footgun. The\nepic completion-verifier flagged this as unmet. (Remediation of epic gnu-whale-ichor to\nfull AC coverage; see session_log fanatical-gentling-bushbaby.)\n\n## What\nAdd a shared guard `reject_private_key_material(values: list[str])` in\n`src/rebar/_commands/identity.py` that raises `CommandError` if any value contains a\nprivate-key PEM/OpenSSH header — matching (case-insensitive) any of:\n`-----BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----`, `-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----`,\n`-----BEGIN EC PRIVATE KEY-----`, `-----BEGIN DSA PRIVATE KEY-----`,\n`-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----`, `-----BEGIN ENCRYPTED PRIVATE KEY-----` (i.e. the generic\n`BEGIN … PRIVATE KEY` family). Call it:\n- in `create_identity_core` on the `keys` list BEFORE `create_core` appends the CREATE\n  event (no event written on rejection);\n- in `add_identity_key` on the `public_key` BEFORE the KEY_ADD event is appended.\nA legitimate authorized-keys public line (`ssh-ed25519 AAAA…`) passes unchanged.\n\n## Scope\nIn: the `reject_private_key_material` guard + its two call sites (identity CREATE keys[]\nand KEY_ADD public_key). Out: any other behavior. The guard function lives in the ddbe\ncommit (558); the `add_identity_key` call site lives in the e165 commit (563) — both are\namended (the guard fn is defined in 558, so 563 can call it).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `create_identity(name, email, keys=[<a string containing \"BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE\n  KEY\">])` raises (CommandError/RebarError) and appends NO event (store unchanged); a test\n  asserts the raise and that no identity was created.\n- [ ] `add_identity_key(identity, <a private-key string>)` raises and appends no KEY_ADD\n  event (test).\n- [ ] A normal authorized-keys public line (`ssh-ed25519 AAAA…`) is accepted by both\n  `create_identity(keys=[…])` and `add_identity_key` (test).\n- [ ] The guard matches the common private-key header family case-insensitively\n  (parametrized test over the RSA/EC/DSA/OPENSSH/PKCS8/ENCRYPTED headers).\n\n## file_impact\n- `src/rebar/_commands/identity.py` (reject_private_key_material guard + create/key-add call sites)","id":"401a-0802-8469-4b93","parent_id":"e68d-b701-4dd9-47aa","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"identity: reject private-key material at the identity write-gate (epic AC1)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783901877003482001,"uuid":"55608d8b-fac2-4a3e-9e97-a5cff4f012a4"}